[VersionToken "437f9690585dcc41eec5b4f1eb48610103f2d3e8cac2d0deb6b1d4f482515ad0"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{You dealt this hand.  

With 13 points and a good Major suit you naturally open 1\S. Partner responds 3\H.  

We are playing strong jump-shifts by Responder so partner is showing 17+ points. However, you are still stuck with your minimum opening so you just rebid 3\S. Partner bids 4NT. What is your reply? 

He asks for Aces so you bid 5\H showing 2. He now bids 5NT.  

You have no King. So you reply 6\C and partner bids 6NT (safer than 6\S).}

